HLS 26RS-5644 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 319
BY REPRESENTATIVE SAWYER
RETIREMENT/FIREFIGHTERS: Requests the actuary for the legislative auditor, in
consultation with the actuaries of the two retirement systems, to study the cost and
feasibility of merging firefighter members of the Baton Rouge City Parish
Employees' Retirement System into the Firefighters' Retirement System
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the actuary for the legislative auditor, in consultation with the actuaries
3 for the two retirement systems, to perform the actuarial investigation required by
4 R.S. 11:2260(A)(11)(d) and report findings relative to the cost and feasibility of
5 merging firefighter members of the Baton Rouge City Parish Employees' Retirement
6 System into the Firefighters' Retirement System.
7 WHEREAS, on January 1, 1980, the Firefighters' Retirement System was established
8 for the purpose of providing retirement allowances and other benefits to firemen employed
9 by any municipality, parish, or fire protection district of the state of Louisiana; and
10 WHEREAS, during its June 30, 2025, actuarial funding valuation, the Firefighters'
11 Retirement System achieved an actuarial funding status of over eighty-six percent; and
12 WHEREAS, the Firefighters' Retirement System is committed to actuarially sound
13 funding and has taken meaningful steps to ensure the sustainability of the defined benefit
14 plan while serving one hundred and forty employers and over eight thousand five hundred
15 members; and
16 WHEREAS, the Baton Rouge City Parish Employees' Retirement System is a public
17 pension fund based in Baton Rouge, Louisiana; and
18 WHEREAS, during its most recent actuarial funding valuation, the Baton Rouge
19 City Parish Employees' Retirement System had a funding ratio of sixty-four percent; and
