1 WHEREAS, the firefighters of the city of Baton Rouge and their beneficiaries
2 deserve a pension that is actuarially funded throughout the lifetime of the members and their
3 survivors; and
4 WHEREAS, retirement plans within the Baton Rouge City Parish Employees'
5 Retirement System have different eligibility requirements and accrual rates depending upon
6 when a firefighter was hired; and
7 WHEREAS, the retirement eligibility requirements and accrual rates are uniform for
8 all members of the Firefighters' Retirement System.
9 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
10 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the actuary for the legislative auditor,
11 in consultation with the actuaries for the two retirement systems, to perform the actuarial
12 investigation required by R.S. 11:2260(A)(11)(d) and to report findings relative to the cost
13 and feasibility of merging firefighter members of the Baton Rouge City Parish Employees'
14 Retirement System into the Firefighters' Retirement System.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the legislative auditor shall submit a report of
16 the results of the actuarial investigation to the House Committee on Retirement no later than
17 January 15, 2027.
